{"key":"post-7483987","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7483987</id>\n<content>You're supposed to turn down the heat when you hear the first rattle.  In fact, I try to stay ahead of the curve by turning down the heat when the steam first starts to escape from under the weight.  If you'll adjust the stove burner so a bit of steam escapes the nozzle, but it doesn't rattle, you'll have about 14.5 psi, and it will be nearly silent.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7483995</next>\n<prev>7483980</prev>\n<first>7483960</first>\n<last>7489137</last>\n<when>1191506484</when>\n<utime>10/04/07 05:01 PM</utime>\n</post>"}